Perceptron and activations
Perceptron: \[ y = f\!\left(\sum_{i=1}^{n} w_i x_i + b\right) \]
Activation functions: - Sigmoid: \(\sigma(z) = \frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}}\) (probabilities) - ReLU: \(\max(0, z)\) (hidden layers) - Softmax: \(\text{softmax}(z_i) = \frac{e^{z_i}}{\sum_j e^{z_j}}\) (multi‚Äëclass)
# Perceptron skeleton for intuition (NumPy)
class Perceptron:
    def __init__(self, d):
        self.w = np.random.randn(d)
        self.b = 0.0
    def predict(self, X):
        z = X @ self.w + self.b
        return (z &gt; 0).astype(int)

